<subSubSection pageId="178" pageNumber="179" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="178" pageNumber="179">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="178" pageNumber="179">
The hybrid 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. f., Suppl. Pl. 136. 1782 [&quot; 1781 &quot;]. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1782" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus floridus" order="Solanales" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="floridus">
Convolvulus scoparius 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
floridus
</taxonomicName>
has leaves that are 1.12-4.86 mm wide, so intermediate in width between the parents. The inflorescence is generally compound unlike the simple inflorescences of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. f., Suppl. Pl. 135. 1782 [&quot; 1781 &quot;]. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1782" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus scoparius" order="Solanales" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scoparius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">Convolvulus scoparius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but less branched than that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="L. f., Suppl. Pl. 136. 1782 [&quot; 1781 &quot;]. (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1782" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus floridus" order="Solanales" pageId="178" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="floridus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="178" pageNumber="179">Convolvulus floridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
